WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.015 --> 00:00:08.747
All right. we're almost home.

2
00:00:25.171 --> 00:00:26.825
Calm down. boy.

3
00:00:41.976 --> 00:00:43.360
It's right up here.

4
00:00:52.285 --> 00:00:54.461
You really think
it's worth 10 grand?

5
00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:50.176
Oh. my God.

6
00:01:50.367 --> 00:01:51.387
What?

7
00:01:51.668 --> 00:01:53.365
Remember Andrea McHugh?

8
00:01:53.514 --> 00:01:56.117
Blue mohawk. threw a brick
through a Starbucks window?

9
00:01:56.142 --> 00:01:58.161
The girl who stole a cop car
sophomore year?

10
00:01:58.186 --> 00:02:00.708
- How could I forget?
- Yeah. look at this.

11
00:02:02.349 --> 00:02:07.006
- No way that's her.
- # Blessed. # Live Laugh Love.

12
00:02:07.731 --> 00:02:10.012
So much for getting
out of small town life.

13
00:02:10.037 --> 00:02:12.517
- Seriously.
- Three kids under five.

14
00:02:12.682 --> 00:02:13.848
That's a handful.

15
00:02:13.943 --> 00:02:16.583
Honey. if I ever suggest
coordinating sleepwear.

16
00:02:16.713 --> 00:02:18.903
you have permission to leave me
and take full custody.

17
00:02:18.928 --> 00:02:20.418
Honey. I would
not need permission.

18
00:02:21.011 --> 00:02:22.933
That's what I love about you.

19
00:02:23.001 --> 00:02:24.286
My devastating charm?

20
00:02:24.340 --> 00:02:26.364
We both hate the same things.

21
00:02:31.121 --> 00:02:33.011
I might need the car today.

22
00:02:33.036 --> 00:02:36.477
Is it cool if I drive. and
I can just drop you at 26 Fed?

23
00:02:36.688 --> 00:02:38.820
- You know. you take the car.
- I'll take the subway.

24
00:02:39.002 --> 00:02:41.028
What? You hate the subway.

25
00:02:41.053 --> 00:02:42.508
We both hate the subway.
See above.

26
00:02:42.533 --> 00:02:43.911
Yeah. fully aware. I just...

27
00:02:43.936 --> 00:02:46.168
I actually have to go Uptown
today. so it'll be easier.

28
00:02:46.401 --> 00:02:47.619
What's Uptown?

29
00:02:49.016 --> 00:02:50.757
- This case.
- I gotta talk to this guy.

30
00:02:50.782 --> 00:02:53.307
He's threatening
to recant his testimony.

31
00:02:54.012 --> 00:02:55.403
So. Uptown I go.

32
00:02:56.404 --> 00:02:57.404
Okay.

33
00:02:57.514 --> 00:02:59.212
What am I looking at. Malcolm?

34
00:02:59.237 --> 00:03:00.518
That's what I want to know.

35
00:03:00.543 --> 00:03:02.328
Something made
this crater last night.

36
00:03:02.430 --> 00:03:04.998
Radiation signatures consistent
with a power source.

37
00:03:05.158 --> 00:03:07.225
not a meteor. not debris.

38
00:03:07.897 --> 00:03:10.772
- Something that was built.
- Can I see what's left of it?

39
00:03:10.797 --> 00:03:13.278
- That's just it.
- Someone got here before us.

40
00:03:13.487 --> 00:03:16.359
Couple someones. actually.
One's in the morgue.

41
00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:19.781
And the other. well.
whatever made this crater.

42
00:03:19.806 --> 00:03:21.155
they've got it now.

43
00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:22.878
And we've checked with
everyone on our end.

44
00:03:22.903 --> 00:03:24.469
It wasn't Canadian.

45
00:03:24.701 --> 00:03:26.616
- So?
- Are you asking if it's ours?

46
00:03:26.685 --> 00:03:27.730
Now that you mention it.

47
00:03:27.755 --> 00:03:29.116
Malcolm.
I'm finding out about this

48
00:03:29.141 --> 00:03:30.702
at the same time
that you're telling me.

49
00:03:30.727 --> 00:03:32.277
That's what you'd say
if it was yours.

50
00:03:32.302 --> 00:03:34.874
- And you're a good liar.
- Yes and yes.

51
00:03:35.085 --> 00:03:37.259
But in this case. it has
the advantage of being true.

52
00:03:37.284 --> 00:03:39.939
If this turns out to be
American technology

53
00:03:39.964 --> 00:03:42.013
- that fell out of the sky...
- Malcolm.

54
00:03:42.038 --> 00:03:44.171
And you are now in
any way covering up.

55
00:03:44.833 --> 00:03:46.614
we're going to have
a serious problem.

56
00:03:47.122 --> 00:03:48.413
And I'm not someone that

57
00:03:48.438 --> 00:03:49.998
you want to have
a serious problem with.

58
00:03:50.023 --> 00:03:52.306
I thought Canadians
were supposed to be polite.

59
00:03:52.331 --> 00:03:55.029
That is an outdated
and offensive stereotype.

60
00:03:58.606 --> 00:03:59.677
All right.

61
00:04:00.976 --> 00:04:02.716
Let's gather the troops.

62
00:04:03.037 --> 00:04:05.605
So an unknown projectile
of unknown origin.

63
00:04:05.630 --> 00:04:08.160
with unknown payload.
emitting unknown amounts

64
00:04:08.185 --> 00:04:10.317
of deadly radiation.
is currently in unknown hands.

65
00:04:10.342 --> 00:04:12.755
Well. at least
we know our known unknowns.

66
00:04:12.780 --> 00:04:14.699
Whose is it?
Anyone call the lost and found?

67
00:04:14.724 --> 00:04:17.857
- Nobody's claimed it.
- Any ideas on what it is?

68
00:04:17.940 --> 00:04:19.661
It could be a weather balloon.

69
00:04:19.685 --> 00:04:21.737
Like the one the military
shot over South Carolina.

70
00:04:21.786 --> 00:04:23.036
courtesy of China?

71
00:04:23.061 --> 00:04:25.106
Or it could be a stealth drone.

72
00:04:25.174 --> 00:04:26.550
meaning one of ours.

73
00:04:26.575 --> 00:04:29.072
Meaning an illegal U.S.-run
surveillance program.

74
00:04:29.159 --> 00:04:30.160
More like unsanctioned.

75
00:04:30.185 --> 00:04:31.955
We don't like labels
here at the CIA.

76
00:04:31.994 --> 00:04:33.780
If it is ours.
we've just stumbled

77
00:04:33.805 --> 00:04:36.494
onto a massive diplomatic
incident with Canada.

78
00:04:36.636 --> 00:04:38.688
- Well. there...
- there is another possibility.

79
00:04:38.713 --> 00:04:40.322
I mean. the...
the radiation signatures

80
00:04:40.347 --> 00:04:43.521
are inconsistent with standard
propulsion and electronics.

81
00:04:43.546 --> 00:04:44.744
Please don't say aliens.

82
00:04:44.769 --> 00:04:46.049
With the amount of energy output

83
00:04:46.074 --> 00:04:48.612
these things are emitting.
I mean. it... it... it...

84
00:04:50.246 --> 00:04:53.283
It's probably not aliens.
That's... that's what I'm saying.

85
00:04:53.346 --> 00:04:54.594
Whatever caused that crater.

86
00:04:54.619 --> 00:04:56.049
we need to find out who took it.

87
00:04:56.074 --> 00:04:58.305
If it was ours
and it's been recovered.

88
00:04:58.461 --> 00:05:00.063
it's embarrassing.
but it's contained.

89
00:05:00.088 --> 00:05:02.039
Yeah. but if someone
got there first.

90
00:05:02.064 --> 00:05:03.860
it could already be
on the black market.

91
00:05:04.047 --> 00:05:05.133
I'll make some calls.

92
00:05:05.158 --> 00:05:06.469
I'll try my government contacts.

93
00:05:06.494 --> 00:05:09.193
And let's bring in Kevin Turner
from Counter Terrorism.

94
00:05:25.954 --> 00:05:28.235
I think I found
what made your crater.

95
00:05:29.675 --> 00:05:31.405
Where did you get these?

96
00:05:32.105 --> 00:05:34.453
Would you believe me if
I said they fell off a truck?

97
00:05:36.203 --> 00:05:38.141
Must have been a weird truck.

98
00:05:39.391 --> 00:05:41.649
Looks like a low Earth
orbit satellite.

99
00:05:41.862 --> 00:05:44.711
Most of it burned up. but
that core was built to survive.

100
00:05:45.043 --> 00:05:47.741
Whose is it.
if you had to guess?

101
00:05:48.299 --> 00:05:51.204
Russian. Chinese. Indian. maybe.

102
00:05:51.229 --> 00:05:53.008
What's it matter?

103
00:05:55.455 --> 00:05:57.076
I have a team out in the field

104
00:05:57.101 --> 00:05:59.234
trying to secure this thing.

105
00:05:59.368 --> 00:06:01.439
I don't know who
they might bump into.

106
00:06:01.569 --> 00:06:04.471
I'll look into it.
see if I can track it.

107
00:06:04.496 --> 00:06:06.642
figure out who launched it.

108
00:06:11.860 --> 00:06:13.648
You told Katie
you're going Uptown

109
00:06:13.673 --> 00:06:15.513
because a witness is
recanting their testimony?

110
00:06:15.549 --> 00:06:17.119
It was the first thing
I could think of.

111
00:06:17.144 --> 00:06:18.681
Jeez. mate. less is more.

112
00:06:18.725 --> 00:06:20.174
It's the details
that trip you up.

113
00:06:20.299 --> 00:06:21.366
Have you still not told her

114
00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:22.662
you're working
for the fusion cell?

115
00:06:22.686 --> 00:06:23.881
I don't want her
worrying about me.

116
00:06:23.905 --> 00:06:26.143
She's a worrier.
I hate lying to her.

117
00:06:26.168 --> 00:06:27.623
Well. you'll get used to it.

118
00:06:27.648 --> 00:06:29.628
Yeah. that's what
I'm worried about.

119
00:06:29.653 --> 00:06:30.950
This is her.

120
00:06:30.975 --> 00:06:32.792
Sixth sense. every time.

121
00:06:32.863 --> 00:06:33.995
All right. well. take it.

122
00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:35.354
I'll only be
a couple of minutes.

123
00:06:35.379 --> 00:06:37.729
- And less is more.
- Yeah.

124
00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:40.737
Hey. honey.

125
00:06:41.488 --> 00:06:43.446
Yeah. I just got Uptown.
What's up?

126
00:06:58.312 --> 00:07:00.445
You're looking for Nigel.

127
00:07:00.671 --> 00:07:02.039
- Yeah.
- Is he in?

128
00:07:02.180 --> 00:07:04.883
Blew his ACL. pickleball.

129
00:07:05.088 --> 00:07:06.193
Vicious sport.

130
00:07:06.218 --> 00:07:08.219
- I told him to stick to chess.
- Yeah.

131
00:07:08.476 --> 00:07:10.219
Something I can help you with?

132
00:07:11.048 --> 00:07:13.211
It's a very particular request.

133
00:07:13.236 --> 00:07:14.829
I normally just deal with him.

134
00:07:15.493 --> 00:07:16.516
Try me.

135
00:07:17.655 --> 00:07:18.665
Okay.

136
00:07:19.969 --> 00:07:23.321
Where can I find a copy of
Chekhov's "The Burial Mound"?

137
00:07:23.712 --> 00:07:27.803
Neverland. maybe.
or the lost city of Atlantis.

138
00:07:28.012 --> 00:07:29.595
It doesn't exist.

139
00:07:30.595 --> 00:07:33.032
All right.
how about "Ben-Hur." 1933.

140
00:07:33.057 --> 00:07:34.954
first Modern Library edition?

141
00:07:44.975 --> 00:07:47.513
Someone must have misplaced it.

142
00:07:48.054 --> 00:07:50.821
Now you can put up
your sneaky little bat signal

143
00:07:50.846 --> 00:07:53.458
to whoever the hell you're
trying to communicate with.

144
00:07:53.627 --> 00:07:54.693
Thank you.

145
00:07:55.478 --> 00:07:56.498
Evelyn.

146
00:07:56.839 --> 00:07:59.323
But like I said.
I might not be here next time.

147
00:07:59.348 --> 00:08:03.490
So this electricity
crackling between us...

148
00:08:03.938 --> 00:08:05.287
Don't get used to it.

149
00:08:19.738 --> 00:08:21.102
Our mystery item.

150
00:08:21.127 --> 00:08:22.730
A satellite fell out of orbit.

151
00:08:22.755 --> 00:08:24.549
Most of it burned up
upon re-entry

152
00:08:24.574 --> 00:08:26.533
or shattered into fragments.
except the battery.

153
00:08:26.584 --> 00:08:28.529
Most satellites are
powered by solar panels.

154
00:08:28.554 --> 00:08:31.165
This one was powered
by an enriched cesium core.

155
00:08:31.355 --> 00:08:33.262
- A nuclear battery.
- Yeah.

156
00:08:33.287 --> 00:08:36.691
So you're saying somebody
put a nuclear device in space?

157
00:08:36.788 --> 00:08:39.487
Cesium-137. to be precise.

158
00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:42.736
So you're aware cesium-137
has roughly ten half-lives

159
00:08:42.761 --> 00:08:46.073
before its radioactivity
diminishes to safe levels?

160
00:08:46.631 --> 00:08:49.616
Sorry. in layman's terms.
that simply means that it's a...

161
00:08:49.641 --> 00:08:52.459
Dirty bomb with that material
could irradiate Times Square

162
00:08:52.484 --> 00:08:54.647
- for 300 years. give or take.
- Yes. exactly.

163
00:08:54.672 --> 00:08:55.884
Certainly. as you can imagine.

164
00:08:55.909 --> 00:08:57.109
there are plenty
of terror groups

165
00:08:57.133 --> 00:08:58.334
who'd love
to get their hands on it.

166
00:08:58.358 --> 00:08:59.364
Rogue nations too.

167
00:08:59.396 --> 00:09:00.833
Do we know who sent it up?

168
00:09:00.904 --> 00:09:02.850
That's not exactly
my department.

169
00:09:04.866 --> 00:09:06.780
There are over 13.000
satellites in orbit

170
00:09:06.805 --> 00:09:09.417
operated by 80 countries.
It might take me just a minute.

171
00:09:09.527 --> 00:09:11.116
You're doing great.

172
00:09:12.022 --> 00:09:13.623
Colin. any word
from your contacts?

173
00:09:13.648 --> 00:09:14.683
No. not yet.

174
00:09:14.708 --> 00:09:15.985
But let's hope he gets in touch

175
00:09:16.010 --> 00:09:18.317
before this thing
hits the open market.

176
00:10:17.660 --> 00:10:19.027
Nice place you got here.

177
00:10:22.136 --> 00:10:23.847
Excellent bourbon.

178
00:10:24.473 --> 00:10:25.691
Jonah.

179
00:10:26.242 --> 00:10:28.766
- You got my signal. then?
- I did.

180
00:10:28.963 --> 00:10:31.800
And I believe I have something
you're looking for.

181
00:10:44.149 --> 00:10:46.326
So what. you're an amateur
photographer now. are you?

182
00:10:46.624 --> 00:10:48.408
I'm thinking about
turning professional.

183
00:10:48.844 --> 00:10:50.010
Who's your friend?

184
00:10:50.035 --> 00:10:51.891
Fellow literature enthusiast.

185
00:10:51.954 --> 00:10:53.820
Looks like a Fed.

186
00:10:54.402 --> 00:10:55.577
How's retirement?

187
00:10:55.609 --> 00:10:56.687
Boring.

188
00:10:57.908 --> 00:11:00.520
I even considered starting
a war to pass the time.

189
00:11:00.545 --> 00:11:03.328
- I thought you liked wars.
- I like war profiteering.

190
00:11:03.353 --> 00:11:04.983
And right now it sounds like

191
00:11:05.008 --> 00:11:08.203
you have a very expensive
problem on your hands.

192
00:11:08.805 --> 00:11:09.988
What have you heard?

193
00:11:10.013 --> 00:11:13.016
Nuclear-powered satellite
scattered across Nova Scotia.

194
00:11:13.240 --> 00:11:14.981
but the battery's missing.

195
00:11:15.052 --> 00:11:17.508
with enough cesium
to level ten city blocks.

196
00:11:17.533 --> 00:11:20.641
The seller.
the one who found it.

197
00:11:21.202 --> 00:11:22.682
is Mateo Kola.

198
00:11:24.126 --> 00:11:25.737
Albanian organized crime.

199
00:11:25.762 --> 00:11:28.194
Controls much of the
smuggling in Eastern Canada.

200
00:11:28.219 --> 00:11:32.136
Some local found the battery.
contacted Mateo for a payday.

201
00:11:32.235 --> 00:11:34.890
he killed her.
and grabbed it for himself.

202
00:11:35.303 --> 00:11:37.359
Well. I always admire
an entrepreneur.

203
00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:39.134
He has a network here
in New York.

204
00:11:39.159 --> 00:11:42.172
He's looking for a buyer to
take it off his hands tomorrow

205
00:11:42.301 --> 00:11:45.484
at the low. low price
of $50 million.

206
00:11:45.540 --> 00:11:47.585
- Is that all?
- Bargain.

207
00:11:47.693 --> 00:11:50.130
Any chatter on Telegram.
Discord?

208
00:11:50.201 --> 00:11:51.500
Usual suspects.

209
00:11:51.532 --> 00:11:53.977
Terrorists. rogue states.

210
00:11:54.002 --> 00:11:56.492
some hedge fund guy
in Montana with a bunker.

211
00:11:56.679 --> 00:11:58.077
Nuclear is the new black...?

212
00:11:58.102 --> 00:11:59.893
But no one with the ability

213
00:11:59.918 --> 00:12:02.355
to pull together
that kind of cash so quickly.

214
00:12:04.758 --> 00:12:05.797
Right.

215
00:12:05.914 --> 00:12:07.578
Now I know why you
skipped the phone call

216
00:12:07.603 --> 00:12:09.217
and made
the personal appearance.

217
00:12:09.242 --> 00:12:11.969
Well. the CIA does have
a long and...

218
00:12:12.274 --> 00:12:15.344
storied history of overpaying.

219
00:12:17.304 --> 00:12:19.773
I'd love nothing more
than to simply

220
00:12:19.875 --> 00:12:21.242
make the introduction

221
00:12:21.267 --> 00:12:23.367
and help you take it
off the market.

222
00:12:25.922 --> 00:12:27.584
I think it's a solid plan.

223
00:12:27.609 --> 00:12:29.347
It's a lot of money
for the U.S. government

224
00:12:29.372 --> 00:12:31.442
to be throwing at
an ex-cop-turned-arms-dealer.

225
00:12:31.467 --> 00:12:33.273
- OK. fine.
- Jonah Le'Roux is a drunk.

226
00:12:33.298 --> 00:12:34.510
And he is a shifty bastard.

227
00:12:34.535 --> 00:12:37.059
But when money's involved.
he's reliable.

228
00:12:37.133 --> 00:12:38.535
What other choice
do we have. Nikki?

229
00:12:38.560 --> 00:12:40.735
If a terrorist group get their
hands on this nuclear battery...

230
00:12:40.759 --> 00:12:42.102
The seller. Mateo Kola.

231
00:12:42.127 --> 00:12:44.668
known for making
undercover agents disappear.

232
00:12:44.693 --> 00:12:46.164
I can maintain my cover.

233
00:12:46.189 --> 00:12:47.468
We know where Mateo
is going to be

234
00:12:47.492 --> 00:12:48.758
when the sale is happening.

235
00:12:48.783 --> 00:12:51.303
Why not give Jonah
the courtesy of a finder's fee

236
00:12:51.328 --> 00:12:53.460
and send the Nuclear
Emergency Support Team

237
00:12:53.485 --> 00:12:54.742
to recover the battery?

238
00:12:54.767 --> 00:12:55.789
We can't involve NEST.

239
00:12:55.814 --> 00:12:57.166
we can't involve other agencies.

240
00:12:57.191 --> 00:12:58.951
not until we have the nuke
in our possession.

241
00:12:58.976 --> 00:13:00.215
We've got to be delicate
about this.

242
00:13:00.239 --> 00:13:01.898
You can't hunt truffles
with a backhoe.

243
00:13:01.923 --> 00:13:04.344
Just to be clear. you're the
truffle pig in this metaphor.

244
00:13:04.625 --> 00:13:06.680
It is a volatile
nuclear battery.

245
00:13:06.705 --> 00:13:08.906
- NEST uses precision.
- We go in with weapons hot...

246
00:13:08.931 --> 00:13:10.792
- I'm totally confident.
- I have no doubt.

247
00:13:10.817 --> 00:13:11.961
Colin's right.

248
00:13:12.818 --> 00:13:15.865
The only way to get eyes on
the device is to stage a buy.

249
00:13:15.890 --> 00:13:18.437
The only way to do that
is with Colin's asset.

250
00:13:18.632 --> 00:13:20.891
It's the safest way to get
Mateo to produce the nuke.

251
00:13:20.917 --> 00:13:23.414
Let us do that. then send NEST
in to make the recovery.

252
00:13:30.665 --> 00:13:31.867
I like it.

253
00:13:32.836 --> 00:13:34.249
That's all it takes. is it?

254
00:13:34.274 --> 00:13:35.690
Bill signs off and we're a go?

255
00:13:35.715 --> 00:13:37.367
Just take the win.

256
00:13:38.974 --> 00:13:40.497
Walk me through it
one more time.

257
00:13:41.015 --> 00:13:42.023
Okay.

258
00:13:44.413 --> 00:13:47.372
I'll check into the hotel
as Joel Andrews. the buyer.

259
00:13:47.397 --> 00:13:49.922
a bag man for a rogue nation
trying to level up.

260
00:13:49.947 --> 00:13:51.025
And Bill?

261
00:13:51.050 --> 00:13:52.394
Bill will be my muscle.

262
00:13:52.419 --> 00:13:54.026
Me personally. I thought
I could have pulled off

263
00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:55.729
international
terrorist financier. but..

264
00:13:55.932 --> 00:13:57.510
You know how he gets.

265
00:13:57.535 --> 00:13:58.971
Jonah will be there
as my broker.

266
00:13:58.996 --> 00:14:01.337
He'll make the introduction
to Mateo at the set time.

267
00:14:01.362 --> 00:14:02.432
Joel Andrews.

268
00:14:02.457 --> 00:14:03.940
And how do you
check the merchandise?

269
00:14:03.965 --> 00:14:05.010
I mean. you can't exactly

270
00:14:05.035 --> 00:14:06.459
check the tires
on nuclear material.

271
00:14:06.484 --> 00:14:08.362
That's why I'm taking
my science advisor.

272
00:14:10.268 --> 00:14:11.557
You want to bring Gina
on the op?

273
00:14:11.582 --> 00:14:12.657
She's an analyst.

274
00:14:12.682 --> 00:14:14.438
She's the only one of us
who knows the difference

275
00:14:14.462 --> 00:14:16.290
between a nuclear reactor
and a hair dryer.

276
00:14:16.333 --> 00:14:17.689
I need her in the field on this.

277
00:14:17.714 --> 00:14:18.620
Thank you.

278
00:14:18.645 --> 00:14:20.079
OK. but at the
first sign of danger.

279
00:14:20.104 --> 00:14:21.518
I'm sending in reinforcements.

280
00:14:21.543 --> 00:14:23.937
And I'd expect nothing less.

281
00:14:28.448 --> 00:14:30.232
Any trends I should know about?

282
00:14:30.679 --> 00:14:32.333
Faux suede is coming back.

283
00:14:32.358 --> 00:14:33.971
I didn't realize it ever left.

284
00:14:36.905 --> 00:14:38.917
Mateo's leaving the hotel.

285
00:14:40.202 --> 00:14:42.248
He might be going
to retrieve the battery.

286
00:14:42.273 --> 00:14:43.675
We need ears in his room

287
00:14:43.700 --> 00:14:45.150
so we know when
he brings it back in.

288
00:14:45.175 --> 00:14:47.036
There's no way he'd leave
his room unattended.

289
00:14:47.060 --> 00:14:48.757
We could bug the room next door.

290
00:14:48.797 --> 00:14:50.081
Directional mic in the vent?

291
00:14:50.233 --> 00:14:51.365
Sorry. for a moment there.

292
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:52.911
I thought
my comms stopped working.

293
00:14:52.935 --> 00:14:54.695
'cause you actually
sounded like a spy. Bill.

294
00:14:58.190 --> 00:15:00.646
I can go to the front desk.
get his room number.

295
00:15:00.671 --> 00:15:02.235
Zeeb said
he would hack the system.

296
00:15:02.260 --> 00:15:03.661
Yeah. that's gonna
take 30 minutes.

297
00:15:03.685 --> 00:15:05.078
I can do it in two.

298
00:15:14.850 --> 00:15:16.815
What are you doing?

299
00:15:21.485 --> 00:15:22.747
OK. fine.

300
00:15:22.772 --> 00:15:25.096
I'm excited to be
out in the field.

301
00:15:25.223 --> 00:15:27.759
Three years running background
checks and threat assessments.

302
00:15:27.784 --> 00:15:29.009
What do you expect?

303
00:15:29.034 --> 00:15:30.581
Let her work.

304
00:15:31.278 --> 00:15:32.339
Okay.

305
00:15:33.121 --> 00:15:35.784
One slip. that's all it takes.

306
00:15:36.202 --> 00:15:38.776
And it's not always you
that pays.

307
00:15:53.752 --> 00:15:55.667
Damn it. Mateo. where are you?

308
00:15:55.692 --> 00:15:56.824
I drove all the way up here

309
00:15:56.849 --> 00:15:58.275
and you don't even
answer the phone?

310
00:15:58.300 --> 00:15:59.737
What am I supposed to do?

311
00:15:59.762 --> 00:16:02.721
It's like you have
no respect for me at all.

312
00:16:03.092 --> 00:16:05.051
You know what? Whatever.
I don't even care.

313
00:16:05.076 --> 00:16:07.659
I hope that you're having
a great time.

314
00:16:08.064 --> 00:16:10.784
- Are you all right. miss?
- Oh. my God.

315
00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:12.877
I am so sorry.

316
00:16:12.902 --> 00:16:15.175
I'm just...
I'm looking for my boyfriend.

317
00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:16.658
Boyfriend. boyfriend.

318
00:16:16.683 --> 00:16:18.909
I'm just...
I'm one of many. actually.

319
00:16:18.934 --> 00:16:19.956
So...

320
00:16:21.315 --> 00:16:23.417
You know. he must... he must
have checked in already.

321
00:16:23.442 --> 00:16:25.618
Maybe you can help me
find his room?

322
00:16:25.643 --> 00:16:27.120
Mateo Kola?

323
00:16:27.227 --> 00:16:29.026
Well. I'm really
not supposed to.

324
00:16:29.051 --> 00:16:30.618
I know you guys
have all these rules.

325
00:16:30.643 --> 00:16:32.938
and you look like you're
really good at your job.

326
00:16:32.963 --> 00:16:34.127
It's just...

327
00:16:39.057 --> 00:16:40.479
All right.

328
00:16:47.690 --> 00:16:49.573
Oh. my God. you are a lifesaver.

329
00:16:49.827 --> 00:16:50.870
Thank you.

330
00:16:54.986 --> 00:16:56.945
Poor bastard
never stood a chance.

331
00:17:12.988 --> 00:17:14.362
Maintenance.

332
00:17:14.803 --> 00:17:16.499
You called the front desk.

333
00:17:16.545 --> 00:17:19.378
You smelled gas or something
coming from your vents?

334
00:17:19.603 --> 00:17:21.151
That wasn't me.

335
00:17:22.370 --> 00:17:24.305
- Sorry.
- Next suite. My bad.

336
00:17:24.330 --> 00:17:29.135
Wait... maybe you should
check mine too. just in case.

337
00:17:30.838 --> 00:17:33.737
All right. yeah.
it'll only take a minute.

338
00:17:35.011 --> 00:17:36.143
He'll give it a once-over.

339
00:17:36.168 --> 00:17:37.316
- All right.
- Should be good to go.

340
00:17:37.340 --> 00:17:38.617
You haven't smelled
any gas. have you?

341
00:17:38.641 --> 00:17:40.077
I have not. no.

342
00:17:40.102 --> 00:17:41.582
Yeah. I don't smell
anything either.

343
00:17:41.607 --> 00:17:42.716
so you probably should be good.

344
00:17:42.740 --> 00:17:44.785
Yeah. yeah. I appreciate it.

345
00:17:45.054 --> 00:17:46.099
Well. that's grand.

346
00:17:46.167 --> 00:17:47.526
Our goal is just to try

347
00:17:47.551 --> 00:17:48.944
and keep everyone safe
here today.

348
00:17:48.969 --> 00:17:49.980
Yeah. appreciate it.

349
00:17:50.005 --> 00:17:51.939
Yeah. well. let us know
if you smell anything.

350
00:17:51.964 --> 00:17:53.476
All right. thanks
for checking. gentlemen.

351
00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:55.284
- Yeah. take care. buddy.
- You too. now.

352
00:17:55.425 --> 00:17:56.703
That should catch all the audio

353
00:17:56.727 --> 00:17:58.065
in Mateo's room.

354
00:17:58.165 --> 00:17:59.853
Like I said. keep it simple.

355
00:17:59.878 --> 00:18:01.831
- Hey. guys.
- I can't find Jonah.

356
00:18:01.886 --> 00:18:02.665
What?

357
00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:04.319
I thought he was posted
at the back door.

358
00:18:04.344 --> 00:18:05.780
- And you checked...
- Everywhere.

359
00:18:05.805 --> 00:18:06.893
Even the men's restroom.

360
00:18:06.925 --> 00:18:08.332
Definitely got some
interesting looks there.

361
00:18:08.356 --> 00:18:10.323
I knew we shouldn't
have trusted this guy.

362
00:18:10.849 --> 00:18:12.549
Just go back to the room.
wait there.

363
00:18:12.574 --> 00:18:15.341
I'll take the stairs up
and check the top two floors.

364
00:18:15.366 --> 00:18:17.114
I'll check the bar downstairs.

365
00:18:17.139 --> 00:18:18.880
if he's a drunk like you say.

366
00:19:06.741 --> 00:19:08.770
- Any sign of Jonah?
- No. Where's Bill?

367
00:19:08.795 --> 00:19:10.561
- I don't know.
- His comms have dropped out.

368
00:19:10.586 --> 00:19:12.594
I'm supposed to be meeting
Mateo in his room any minute.

369
00:19:12.618 --> 00:19:14.109
and we've got no one
to make the introduction.

370
00:19:14.133 --> 00:19:15.389
I thought you said
Jonah was reliable.

371
00:19:15.413 --> 00:19:16.980
Please don't quote me.

372
00:19:17.330 --> 00:19:18.968
OK. we need to find them now.

373
00:19:18.993 --> 00:19:21.194
This thing's gone pear-shaped
before it even started.

374
00:19:27.985 --> 00:19:29.760
Who do you work for?

375
00:19:38.741 --> 00:19:40.525
Where did you come from...?

376
00:19:40.678 --> 00:19:42.398
Where... where do
any of us come from?

377
00:19:42.423 --> 00:19:43.897
You know.
when you think about it?

378
00:19:47.530 --> 00:19:48.920
I need him alive.

379
00:19:53.478 --> 00:19:56.853
All right. gentlemen. you...
relax. get some vitamin D.

380
00:19:57.176 --> 00:19:59.376
I'll be back.
And when I do...

381
00:19:59.567 --> 00:20:01.587
you better tell me
everything you know.

382
00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:10.971
Those friends of yours?

383
00:20:10.996 --> 00:20:12.621
I have no idea
who those guys were.

384
00:20:12.646 --> 00:20:14.125
but I knew they'd make you.

385
00:20:14.150 --> 00:20:15.325
I bet you they made you

386
00:20:15.350 --> 00:20:17.147
before you brushed your teeth
this morning.

387
00:20:17.172 --> 00:20:18.973
When you were born.
I bet the doctor said.

388
00:20:18.998 --> 00:20:21.865
look at this perfectly healthy
little federal agent.

389
00:20:23.514 --> 00:20:25.092
Oh. God.

390
00:20:25.256 --> 00:20:27.006
What. did you forget
you were a cop?

391
00:20:27.031 --> 00:20:29.730
Yeah. I was. until
people like you burned me.

392
00:20:31.225 --> 00:20:34.010
Yeah. maybe don't take bribes
next time.

393
00:20:38.264 --> 00:20:39.387
What are you doing?

394
00:20:39.412 --> 00:20:40.983
What's it look like I'm doing?

395
00:20:41.008 --> 00:20:42.966
I'm going to take them out
when they come back.

396
00:20:42.991 --> 00:20:44.973
- Are you crazy?
- What. with IKEA leftovers?

397
00:20:44.998 --> 00:20:46.396
They have guns.
They will kill us.

398
00:20:46.420 --> 00:20:47.850
They would have done it already.

399
00:20:47.898 --> 00:20:49.483
They want to break us.

400
00:20:49.508 --> 00:20:51.728
- Yeah. but they won't.
- Yeah. speak for yourself.

401
00:20:51.753 --> 00:20:53.755
And it's going to hurt
like hell when they try.

402
00:20:53.981 --> 00:20:55.491
We gotta get out of here.

403
00:21:02.843 --> 00:21:05.150
We can escape out the vent.

404
00:21:08.389 --> 00:21:10.565
You going to help me or what?

405
00:21:13.131 --> 00:21:14.660
Well. they couldn't
have just vanished.

406
00:21:14.685 --> 00:21:16.171
They got to be somewhere
at the hotel.

407
00:21:16.225 --> 00:21:17.576
Have Zeeb see if he can access

408
00:21:17.601 --> 00:21:19.037
the hotel security cameras.

409
00:21:19.164 --> 00:21:20.546
Okay. good idea.

410
00:21:20.618 --> 00:21:22.632
What if someone took them?

411
00:21:23.733 --> 00:21:24.821
Well. if they did.

412
00:21:24.846 --> 00:21:26.647
it means they want this thing
more than we do.

413
00:21:26.672 --> 00:21:27.978
And that means. Colin.

414
00:21:28.003 --> 00:21:30.483
that we need you
to approach Mateo now.

415
00:21:30.533 --> 00:21:32.411
Without Jonah there
to make an introduction?

416
00:21:32.436 --> 00:21:33.796
Well. he doesn't know me
from Adam.

417
00:21:33.821 --> 00:21:34.677
Make it work.

418
00:21:34.702 --> 00:21:36.264
Get the battery
and get out of there.

419
00:21:36.390 --> 00:21:38.043
I could pretend to be Jonah.

420
00:21:38.241 --> 00:21:39.907
Won't Mateo be looking for...

421
00:21:39.932 --> 00:21:41.389
- What?
- A man?

422
00:21:41.475 --> 00:21:42.989
They don't know what Jonah is.

423
00:21:43.014 --> 00:21:45.322
We put a bug in their room.
Mateo was talking to his guys.

424
00:21:45.347 --> 00:21:46.696
We know they've never met.

425
00:21:46.721 --> 00:21:49.459
They only ever communicated
over encrypted texts.

426
00:21:49.606 --> 00:21:51.958
Jonah could be a woman.
he could be a man.

427
00:21:51.983 --> 00:21:53.920
or a string quartet.

428
00:21:56.729 --> 00:21:59.889
I didn't join the CIA
to sit on the bench.

429
00:22:00.613 --> 00:22:01.631
Okay.

430
00:22:02.763 --> 00:22:03.886
Go with the flow.

431
00:22:04.403 --> 00:22:07.084
But it's Colin's flow.
You understand?

432
00:22:09.096 --> 00:22:11.053
- Seen. not heard.
- Got it.

433
00:22:13.834 --> 00:22:16.925
All right.
if anything turns in that room.

434
00:22:16.950 --> 00:22:19.373
you follow my cues
and you walk away. OK?

435
00:22:19.537 --> 00:22:20.537
Promise.

436
00:22:21.465 --> 00:22:23.123
Put your glasses on.

437
00:22:48.752 --> 00:22:50.533
- All right.
- Okay.

438
00:22:50.768 --> 00:22:52.552
Want to buy me a drink first?

439
00:22:52.698 --> 00:22:54.830
We were told the meeting
was 2:00 p.m.

440
00:22:55.199 --> 00:22:56.462
Who are you?

441
00:23:09.685 --> 00:23:12.982
Joel Andrews.
Andrews Investments.

442
00:23:15.143 --> 00:23:16.223
And her?

443
00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:18.875
Who do you think I am?

444
00:23:19.009 --> 00:23:20.123
I'm Jonah.

445
00:23:23.673 --> 00:23:24.825
You're Jonah?

446
00:23:26.582 --> 00:23:28.889
Sometimes I'm Jonah.
sometimes I'm Ashley.

447
00:23:28.914 --> 00:23:30.575
You must be Mateo.

448
00:23:31.078 --> 00:23:33.548
OK. now we're done
playing 20 questions.

449
00:23:33.573 --> 00:23:36.310
Can we get to
the business in hand?

450
00:23:36.999 --> 00:23:38.185
Where's the nuke?

451
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:41.529
You think I'm stupid enough
to have it in the room?

452
00:23:42.332 --> 00:23:45.755
I need to see
proof of funds first.

453
00:23:46.712 --> 00:23:49.628
You show me yours.
and I'll show you mine.

454
00:24:00.734 --> 00:24:02.776
There. good enough?

455
00:24:03.733 --> 00:24:06.040
Now where's my nuke?

456
00:24:06.425 --> 00:24:08.986
Patience. patience.

457
00:24:10.326 --> 00:24:14.025
I haven't heard from the
other interested parties yet.

458
00:24:14.255 --> 00:24:15.956
- Hold on.
- Other interested parties?

459
00:24:15.981 --> 00:24:17.186
That wasn't the plan.

460
00:24:17.211 --> 00:24:18.565
Plans change.

461
00:24:18.947 --> 00:24:20.557
just like the price.

462
00:24:21.939 --> 00:24:23.682
It's going up.

463
00:24:24.470 --> 00:24:25.604
Is it?

464
00:24:35.436 --> 00:24:36.756
Are we getting
into a bidding war?

465
00:24:36.781 --> 00:24:37.781
Sounds like it.

466
00:24:37.814 --> 00:24:38.944
What are we going to do?

467
00:24:38.969 --> 00:24:40.927
I mean. there's no way we have
enough for best and final.

468
00:24:40.951 --> 00:24:42.849
That's for Nikki to sort out
with Headquarters.

469
00:24:42.874 --> 00:24:43.890
So what do you think?

470
00:24:43.915 --> 00:24:45.429
You think Jonah
walked us into a trap?

471
00:24:45.569 --> 00:24:46.889
It's the first thing
I'm going to ask him

472
00:24:46.913 --> 00:24:48.397
when we find him.

473
00:24:54.679 --> 00:24:56.702
So how'd you end up
on the other side?

474
00:24:57.905 --> 00:24:59.659
I was the cop
on the brochure. you know?

475
00:24:59.684 --> 00:25:01.311
For the first three years.

476
00:25:01.757 --> 00:25:04.906
Wife. four kids on a cop's
salary. you know the deal.

477
00:25:04.931 --> 00:25:07.760
- It's a real sob story.
- You want to hear it or not?

478
00:25:08.102 --> 00:25:09.999
And not that
this excuses anything.

479
00:25:10.024 --> 00:25:11.547
but everybody was doing it.

480
00:25:11.633 --> 00:25:13.350
Look the other way
for a local dealer.

481
00:25:13.375 --> 00:25:15.116
suddenly. there's food
on the table.

482
00:25:15.141 --> 00:25:16.732
presents under
the Christmas tree.

483
00:25:16.757 --> 00:25:18.187
no one gets hurt.

484
00:25:18.212 --> 00:25:21.093
You could give up this life.
still get your family back.

485
00:25:21.118 --> 00:25:24.015
No. Because... and my wife.
she knew this too...

486
00:25:25.219 --> 00:25:26.343
I liked it.

487
00:25:27.046 --> 00:25:28.069
The money?

488
00:25:28.725 --> 00:25:29.780
The danger.

489
00:25:30.087 --> 00:25:32.263
The never knowing
if I'd make it out alive.

490
00:25:32.545 --> 00:25:35.077
The rush when I did.
And you like it too.

491
00:25:35.225 --> 00:25:37.793
- No.
- No. I'm nothing like that.

492
00:25:37.997 --> 00:25:39.303
Oh. yeah.

493
00:25:39.581 --> 00:25:42.323
OK. you have a woman
back at home?

494
00:25:42.410 --> 00:25:43.675
A wife?

495
00:25:44.705 --> 00:25:45.765
A fiancée.

496
00:25:45.790 --> 00:25:47.922
- OK.
- So you're playing with fire.

497
00:25:48.111 --> 00:25:50.654
You could work a desk job.
coach the soccer team.

498
00:25:50.679 --> 00:25:51.700
be home for dinner.

499
00:25:51.725 --> 00:25:53.707
Instead. you chose to be here
risking everything

500
00:25:53.732 --> 00:25:56.300
while she's back at home
thinking everything is fine

501
00:25:56.325 --> 00:25:58.483
until one day.
she gets a phone call

502
00:25:58.508 --> 00:26:00.833
saying that
you're not coming home.

503
00:26:01.271 --> 00:26:03.795
You're trying to have it
both ways. suit.

504
00:26:03.929 --> 00:26:05.872
And let me tell you.

505
00:26:06.317 --> 00:26:07.520
you can't.

506
00:26:18.313 --> 00:26:20.095
- Finally.
- Oh. yeah.

507
00:26:34.244 --> 00:26:36.029
- Okay.
- I think we got it.

508
00:26:48.258 --> 00:26:49.825
Damn it.

509
00:26:52.306 --> 00:26:53.742
Now what?

510
00:27:01.294 --> 00:27:02.841
Okay. thanks.

511
00:27:03.261 --> 00:27:04.920
Nikki's trying to secure
more funds.

512
00:27:04.945 --> 00:27:06.365
All right. good.

513
00:27:10.744 --> 00:27:12.458
- What. what?
- What is it?

514
00:27:12.887 --> 00:27:13.949
The bar.

515
00:27:14.207 --> 00:27:15.309
Have a look.

516
00:27:15.402 --> 00:27:17.404
Tall guy. big bushy beard.

517
00:27:19.778 --> 00:27:21.465
Yeah. yeah. I see him.

518
00:27:21.628 --> 00:27:23.450
That's Sasha Kotov.

519
00:27:23.936 --> 00:27:25.293
He's FSB.

520
00:27:26.714 --> 00:27:29.465
- Russian intelligence.
- That's not a coincidence.

521
00:27:29.490 --> 00:27:30.981
No. it's not.

522
00:27:31.364 --> 00:27:32.714
He's either here with Mateo

523
00:27:32.740 --> 00:27:34.668
or he's trying
to buy the nuke himself.

524
00:27:34.693 --> 00:27:36.029
What. you think he has
something to do with.

525
00:27:36.053 --> 00:27:36.998
Bill and Jonah missing?

526
00:27:37.023 --> 00:27:38.746
I wouldn't bet against it.

527
00:27:39.459 --> 00:27:41.374
Eliminate the other buyers.

528
00:27:41.507 --> 00:27:43.239
- Eliminate?
- Yeah.

529
00:27:43.581 --> 00:27:45.358
We need to find
Bill and Jonah now.

530
00:27:45.383 --> 00:27:47.059
OK. what about
the nuclear battery?

531
00:27:48.379 --> 00:27:49.594
Where was it written that

532
00:27:49.619 --> 00:27:51.684
two disasters can't hit
at the same time?

533
00:27:52.219 --> 00:27:53.873
Yeah. Colin. still nothing.

534
00:27:54.075 --> 00:27:56.254
OK. well. keep combing
security footage.

535
00:27:56.279 --> 00:27:57.895
let me know the second
you find anything.

536
00:27:57.920 --> 00:27:58.926
You got it.

537
00:27:58.951 --> 00:28:00.518
Zeeb have anything?

538
00:28:00.543 --> 00:28:02.486
Only that Bill and Jonah
never left the building.

539
00:28:02.511 --> 00:28:04.272
- Apart from that...
- OK. well. that's good.

540
00:28:04.297 --> 00:28:06.352
Then we... we search room by room
until we find them.

541
00:28:06.376 --> 00:28:08.727
No. I mean. the second
we go and look for Bill.

542
00:28:08.807 --> 00:28:10.020
we lose eyes on Sasha.

543
00:28:10.045 --> 00:28:11.560
He could just walk out of here
with a nuke.

544
00:28:11.584 --> 00:28:13.780
Well then.
we divide and conquer.

545
00:28:14.066 --> 00:28:16.634
You go for Bill.
I'll distract Sasha at the bar.

546
00:28:16.659 --> 00:28:17.700
No.

547
00:28:17.725 --> 00:28:19.489
- No. Gina. Sorry. no.
- Yes.

548
00:28:19.514 --> 00:28:21.936
No. This guy's been FSB
for the last 20 years.

549
00:28:21.961 --> 00:28:23.788
- It's okay.
- He's a human lie detector.

550
00:28:23.813 --> 00:28:26.946
Stop treating me
like I'm going to break.

551
00:28:27.531 --> 00:28:29.926
I get it. you've been hurt.

552
00:28:30.230 --> 00:28:31.653
You lost someone.

553
00:28:32.386 --> 00:28:33.957
I'm not her.

554
00:28:35.006 --> 00:28:36.793
You know about Toni?

555
00:28:37.764 --> 00:28:40.121
- I'm a big girl. Colin.
- I can do this.

556
00:28:44.574 --> 00:28:45.504
Zeeb?

557
00:28:45.529 --> 00:28:46.835
There's a whole bank of cameras

558
00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:48.504
covering the basement
storage area. B2.

559
00:28:48.529 --> 00:28:50.181
every one of them disabled.

560
00:28:50.486 --> 00:28:52.088
Well. that's not
a coincidence either.

561
00:28:52.126 --> 00:28:53.149
Thanks.

562
00:29:01.871 --> 00:29:04.831
If he makes you.
you walk away immediately.

563
00:29:04.902 --> 00:29:05.902
Yeah.

564
00:29:06.088 --> 00:29:07.667
Nikki's going to kill me.

565
00:29:07.692 --> 00:29:10.259
Well. we might all be
dead anyway. so there's that.

566
00:29:10.608 --> 00:29:11.667
Just...

567
00:29:12.923 --> 00:29:14.707
be careful. please.

568
00:29:15.525 --> 00:29:16.589
Promise.

569
00:29:38.511 --> 00:29:40.013
Drink menu. please.

570
00:29:41.538 --> 00:29:42.864
Sable 6.

571
00:29:43.418 --> 00:29:44.551
The best.

572
00:29:45.739 --> 00:29:46.927
All right then.

573
00:29:47.633 --> 00:29:48.974
I'll get that.
Thank you.

574
00:29:53.458 --> 00:29:55.808
You know. I had a boyfriend
from St. Petersburg.

575
00:29:56.105 --> 00:29:58.927
He loved Sable 6
a little too much.

576
00:29:59.878 --> 00:30:01.122
You...

577
00:30:01.903 --> 00:30:03.509
You spent time in Russia?

578
00:30:03.714 --> 00:30:04.833
Little bit.

579
00:30:05.474 --> 00:30:09.450
I have a love for the country.
The people. not so much.

580
00:30:10.716 --> 00:30:14.489
Maybe I can...
help you change your mind.

581
00:30:15.978 --> 00:30:19.278
You... you visiting here?

582
00:30:20.075 --> 00:30:21.167
With anyone?

583
00:30:21.192 --> 00:30:24.536
I prefer to travel alone.
expect the unexpected.

584
00:30:24.846 --> 00:30:26.075
Yes.

585
00:30:26.771 --> 00:30:29.521
American women
are so independent.

586
00:30:30.883 --> 00:30:32.225
So confident.

587
00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:36.521
And we're open books.
unlike you. a man...

588
00:30:37.364 --> 00:30:40.036
- shrouded in mystery.
- Yeah?

589
00:30:41.550 --> 00:30:43.427
What would you like to know?

590
00:31:21.170 --> 00:31:23.042
I've always loved tigers.

591
00:31:23.172 --> 00:31:25.717
Independent. strong hunters.

592
00:31:25.898 --> 00:31:27.733
They work in the shadows.

593
00:31:27.968 --> 00:31:29.056
Suits you.

594
00:31:29.235 --> 00:31:30.303
Yeah?

595
00:31:30.720 --> 00:31:33.006
So you got me
all figured out...?

596
00:31:34.115 --> 00:31:36.483
Well. I can take a guess.

597
00:31:36.860 --> 00:31:38.811
You're a Russian oligarch.

598
00:31:39.194 --> 00:31:41.265
Here for business
with your mistress.

599
00:31:41.290 --> 00:31:44.006
You brought along
a couple scary men

600
00:31:44.217 --> 00:31:45.787
to keep you company.

601
00:31:46.082 --> 00:31:47.756
Does that sound about right?

602
00:31:48.529 --> 00:31:50.217
No mistress tonight.

603
00:31:51.451 --> 00:31:53.758
Well. you don't need
any protection from me.

604
00:31:54.135 --> 00:31:55.326
Perhaps not.

605
00:31:56.347 --> 00:32:01.787
Perhaps we continue
our conversation in private?

606
00:32:03.400 --> 00:32:05.315
Maybe after
a couple more of these.

607
00:32:07.111 --> 00:32:09.814
You find me so unattractive.

608
00:32:10.058 --> 00:32:12.365
You find me so easy?

609
00:32:15.033 --> 00:32:16.644
No. I'm just meeting up
with a friend.

610
00:32:16.669 --> 00:32:19.323
and I don't want to be rude.
make him wait.

611
00:32:23.907 --> 00:32:26.300
I thought you said
you were traveling alone.

612
00:32:28.307 --> 00:32:29.325
I am.

613
00:32:29.350 --> 00:32:31.744
We ran into each other
in the lobby.

614
00:32:36.409 --> 00:32:39.697
Excuse me a second while
I run to the ladies room?

615
00:32:40.790 --> 00:32:42.792
You're not going anywhere

616
00:32:42.927 --> 00:32:47.018
until I find out
exactly who you are.

617
00:33:56.827 --> 00:33:59.229
Jeez. you two look like
you've been having fun.

618
00:33:59.254 --> 00:34:01.139
We've been
getting to know each other.

619
00:34:01.223 --> 00:34:03.529
- Where's Gina?
- She's running interference.

620
00:34:03.554 --> 00:34:05.585
We gotta get upstairs
and make Mateo an offer.

621
00:34:05.610 --> 00:34:06.959
I did while
you two were down here

622
00:34:06.984 --> 00:34:09.294
- braiding each other's hair.
- What. we got the nuke?

623
00:34:09.319 --> 00:34:10.960
No. there's other buyers.

624
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:12.905
Let me guess.
our new Russian friend?

625
00:34:12.930 --> 00:34:14.497
Sasha Kotov. he's FSB.

626
00:34:14.522 --> 00:34:16.561
- That's not good.
- No. it's exactly what I said.

627
00:34:16.586 --> 00:34:17.935
We need to get to Mateo's suite

628
00:34:17.960 --> 00:34:20.056
and try and close this deal
before anyone else. Here.

629
00:34:20.081 --> 00:34:21.648
Guns go first.

630
00:34:29.969 --> 00:34:31.460
Don't...

631
00:34:37.779 --> 00:34:40.216
- Yeah. man.
- You like the rush.

632
00:34:40.536 --> 00:34:41.546
Let's move.

633
00:34:41.571 --> 00:34:44.399
Yeah. clean yourself up
before you meet your public.

634
00:34:44.806 --> 00:34:46.633
I have my best people on this.

635
00:34:46.658 --> 00:34:48.263
Rest assured
we'll bring the device in.

636
00:34:48.288 --> 00:34:49.848
That might not be possible.

637
00:34:50.077 --> 00:34:51.348
What does that mean?

638
00:34:51.373 --> 00:34:53.985
CSA finished examining
the debris field.

639
00:34:54.675 --> 00:34:57.722
They confirm the satellite is
Russian. but more important.

640
00:34:57.916 --> 00:34:59.787
they analyzed the samples
for radiation.

641
00:34:59.897 --> 00:35:01.942
Positive for radionuclides.

642
00:35:02.076 --> 00:35:03.876
- Get to the point.
- What are you telling me?

643
00:35:03.901 --> 00:35:06.130
All the tests indicate
this thing is leaking.

644
00:35:06.365 --> 00:35:08.216
Well. what does that mean
for my guys?

645
00:35:08.241 --> 00:35:11.151
It means they can't get close
for any extended period of time

646
00:35:11.176 --> 00:35:13.569
or they'll be breathing in
radioactive particles.

647
00:35:13.747 --> 00:35:15.140
It's a death sentence.

648
00:35:15.376 --> 00:35:17.117
And here's the real danger.

649
00:35:17.211 --> 00:35:18.908
A death sentence
wasn't the real danger?

650
00:35:19.005 --> 00:35:20.237
Based on our modeling.

651
00:35:20.262 --> 00:35:22.356
this thing could blow
at any minute.

652
00:35:23.082 --> 00:35:24.083
Okay.

653
00:35:28.480 --> 00:35:29.890
That's radiation poisoning.

654
00:35:29.915 --> 00:35:31.700
Certainly looks like it.

655
00:35:35.877 --> 00:35:36.890
Nikki.

656
00:35:36.915 --> 00:35:38.831
Colin. the nuke is leaking.

657
00:35:39.362 --> 00:35:40.636
Yeah. we're aware.

658
00:35:40.661 --> 00:35:42.573
- What?
- How... are you...

659
00:35:42.598 --> 00:35:45.010
Either that or Mateo
had a serious nut allergy.

660
00:35:45.127 --> 00:35:46.127
He's dead.

661
00:35:46.152 --> 00:35:48.206
He must have had the nuke
on him this entire time.

662
00:35:48.263 --> 00:35:50.659
That's what.
three days' direct exposure?

663
00:35:50.684 --> 00:35:51.698
- Yeah.
- No wonder.

664
00:35:51.723 --> 00:35:53.707
- Well. What about the nuke?
- Have you found it?

665
00:35:53.732 --> 00:35:55.280
No. no. we've looked everywhere.

666
00:35:55.305 --> 00:35:56.567
It's not here.

667
00:35:56.850 --> 00:35:59.307
- Whoa. jeez.
- You.

668
00:35:59.689 --> 00:36:01.252
We checked his pulse.

669
00:36:02.322 --> 00:36:04.799
Mateo. where's the nuke?

670
00:36:05.338 --> 00:36:07.713
Sasha took the nuke.

671
00:36:07.963 --> 00:36:10.182
And he has the girl.

672
00:36:10.330 --> 00:36:12.932
He know she's CIA.

673
00:36:17.708 --> 00:36:19.918
Guys. the NEST team
is on the way to you.

674
00:36:19.983 --> 00:36:22.637
- Where's Gina?
- Yeah. Nikki. gotta go.

675
00:36:22.877 --> 00:36:24.708
Lot of moving pieces.
but we're on it.

676
00:36:25.993 --> 00:36:27.051
Let's go.

677
00:36:32.708 --> 00:36:34.623
NEST team's almost here.

678
00:36:37.151 --> 00:36:38.231
That's her.

679
00:36:39.436 --> 00:36:41.221
And that's got to be the nuke.

680
00:36:41.246 --> 00:36:42.372
Stay here.

681
00:36:42.486 --> 00:36:45.533
Yeah... you kids have fun.

682
00:36:45.558 --> 00:36:47.566
- So what's your plan?
- You're going to kill me now?

683
00:36:47.590 --> 00:36:48.815
No. no. no. no. no.

684
00:36:48.840 --> 00:36:50.622
You're going to die
in a field in Russia

685
00:36:50.647 --> 00:36:52.200
after we get everything we want

686
00:36:52.225 --> 00:36:54.372
from that pretty
little head of yours.

687
00:36:58.578 --> 00:37:00.591
The Russians sent you
to collect their fallen tech.

688
00:37:00.616 --> 00:37:01.985
but you're never
going to get it back.

689
00:37:02.009 --> 00:37:04.153
It's going to melt.
radiation is going to spread.

690
00:37:04.178 --> 00:37:05.867
and millions will be exposed.

691
00:37:05.892 --> 00:37:07.601
NEST team. are you in position?

692
00:37:07.751 --> 00:37:09.344
- Yes. sir.
- Call it.

693
00:37:11.100 --> 00:37:13.319
I'm not getting in there
with that thing.

694
00:37:13.609 --> 00:37:14.733
Take them.

695
00:37:28.163 --> 00:37:29.234
Get out.

696
00:37:50.153 --> 00:37:52.634
- Secure him.
- Let's go.

697
00:37:53.695 --> 00:37:54.710
You Okay?

698
00:37:54.735 --> 00:37:55.520
- Yeah. I'm good.
- Yeah?

699
00:37:55.545 --> 00:37:57.147
This nuke's going to melt
any minute.

700
00:37:57.172 --> 00:37:59.234
Then we need
to evacuate everyone now.

701
00:37:59.320 --> 00:38:01.164
- What? No.
- There's no time.

702
00:38:01.189 --> 00:38:03.348
If it melts down during evac.
we're all dead anyway.

703
00:38:03.373 --> 00:38:05.245
No. we need to
get it out of here.

704
00:38:05.347 --> 00:38:06.398
Yeah.

705
00:38:06.878 --> 00:38:09.156
Passed a quarry two miles back.

706
00:38:10.213 --> 00:38:12.539
I could get this thing
underground.

707
00:38:13.556 --> 00:38:16.484
Jonah. you don't have
to be a hero. man.

708
00:38:17.023 --> 00:38:20.000
- Why not?
- For the first time in my life.

709
00:38:22.604 --> 00:38:23.789
Go home.

710
00:38:24.782 --> 00:38:26.175
See your girl.

711
00:39:29.715 --> 00:39:30.990
Contact Headquarters.

712
00:39:31.015 --> 00:39:33.989
Make sure we debrief them on
all the radiation containment.

713
00:39:52.410 --> 00:39:55.527
I'd... offer
to buy you a drink. but...

714
00:39:55.761 --> 00:39:58.113
But I've had enough vodka
for at least a year?

715
00:39:58.202 --> 00:39:59.301
Yeah.

716
00:40:00.787 --> 00:40:03.550
Look. with Sasha.
that was my call to put you in.

717
00:40:03.575 --> 00:40:04.793
I never should have done that.

718
00:40:04.818 --> 00:40:06.848
No. I know what I signed up for.

719
00:40:07.143 --> 00:40:09.527
Danger is part of the job.

720
00:40:10.309 --> 00:40:12.833
Well. for what it's worth.
you did quite well.

721
00:40:13.056 --> 00:40:15.885
Definitely... trending
in the right direction.

722
00:40:16.152 --> 00:40:18.355
But... more importantly.

723
00:40:19.547 --> 00:40:21.059
what are we going to tell Nikki?

724
00:40:21.463 --> 00:40:23.682
'Cause we need
to get our stories straight.

725
00:40:47.755 --> 00:40:48.935
You're home.

726
00:40:49.257 --> 00:40:51.346
- Yeah. sorry.
- Go back to sleep.

727
00:40:51.629 --> 00:40:52.794
Good day?

728
00:40:54.252 --> 00:40:55.520
Yeah. just long.

729
00:40:56.443 --> 00:40:57.618
I'm gonna shower.

730
00:40:57.643 --> 00:41:00.161
- OK.
- I love you.

731
00:41:01.789 --> 00:41:03.028
Love you too.
